    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a concours-standard 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54B32 3.2L inline-six. This naturally aspirated powerplant, equipped with six individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing, delivers a precise 333 hp. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M differential lock. This example is mechanically flawless: the rear subframe has been proactively reinforced, and the rod bearings were replaced with VAC Motorsports coated shells. The suspension retains its factory-correct geometry with refreshed bushings and Bilstein B6 dampers. Finished in Carbon Black Metallic, the bodywork is free of orange peel or rock chips, while the interior features pristine Nappa leather with zero bolster wear. This is a collector-grade chassis for the discerning driver who demands mechanical transparency and peak performance.",
